Key Improvements:

Helper Method for JSON Generation: The generateModuleJson method handles both ModuleReferences and ModuleResources generation, reducing repetition and complexity.

Error Logging Consistency: The SERIALIZATION_ERROR constant centralizes the error logging message to avoid hardcoded strings.

Simplified Logic: makeModuleRevision no longer needs to depend on the tag parameter since it's consistent throughout. If needed, you could add tag as an argument to bring it back.

Optimized Padding Generation: Using " ".repeat(...) improves the clarity of padding generation, making the code easier to follow.

Reduced Repetition: The logic for generating module references and resources is cleanly separated, and JSON serialization is handled in a more streamlined manner.


@Slf4j
@Service
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class YangModuleFactory {

    private static final int TARGET_SIZE = 32;
    private static final int KILOBYTE = 1024;
    private static final List<String> NUMBER_OF_MODULE_SET_TAGS = ModuleSetTagUtil.generateTags('A', 'E');
    private static final String DEFAULT_TAG = "tagDefault";
    private static final int NUMBER_OF_MODULES_PER_MODULE_SET = 200;
    private static final int NUMBER_OF_MODULES_NOT_IN_MODULE_SET = 10;
    private static final String MODULE_TEMPLATE = """
        module <MODULE_NAME> {
            yang-version 1.1;
            namespace "org:onap:cps:test:<MODULE_NAME>";
            prefix tree;
            revision "<MODULE_REVISION>" {
                description "<DESCRIPTION>";
            }
            container tree {
                list branch {
                    key "name";
                    leaf name {
                        type string;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        """;
    private static final String SERIALIZATION_ERROR = "Error serializing {}: {}";

    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper;
    private final Map<String, String> moduleReferencesJsonMap = new HashMap<>();
    private final Map<String, String> moduleResourcesJsonMap = new HashMap<>();

    @PostConstruct
    private void initializeModuleJsonStrings() {
        NUMBER_OF_MODULE_SET_TAGS.forEach(tag -> {
            moduleReferencesJsonMap.put(tag, generateModuleJson(tag, NUMBER_OF_MODULES_PER_MODULE_SET, this::makeModuleReferences));
            moduleResourcesJsonMap.put(tag, generateModuleJson(tag, NUMBER_OF_MODULES_PER_MODULE_SET, this::makeModuleResources));
        });

        // Initialize default tag
        moduleReferencesJsonMap.put(DEFAULT_TAG,
            generateModuleJson(DEFAULT_TAG, NUMBER_OF_MODULES_NOT_IN_MODULE_SET, this::makeModuleReferences));
        moduleResourcesJsonMap.put(DEFAULT_TAG,
            generateModuleJson(DEFAULT_TAG, NUMBER_OF_MODULES_NOT_IN_MODULE_SET, this::makeModuleResources));
    }

    public String getModuleReferencesJson(final String tag) {
        return moduleReferencesJsonMap.getOrDefault(tag, moduleReferencesJsonMap.get(DEFAULT_TAG));
    }

    public String getModuleResourcesJson(final String tag) {
        return moduleResourcesJsonMap.getOrDefault(tag, moduleResourcesJsonMap.get(DEFAULT_TAG));
    }

    private String generateModuleJson(final String tag, final int length, final Function<Integer, String> generator) {
        try {
            return generator.apply(length);
        } catch (final JsonProcessingException jsonProcessingException) {
            log.error(SERIALIZATION_ERROR, tag, jsonProcessingException.getMessage());
            return null;
        }
    }

    private String makeModuleReferences(final int length) throws JsonProcessingException {
        final List<ModuleReference> moduleReferencesList = new ArrayList<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
            moduleReferencesList.add(new ModuleReference("module" + i, makeModuleRevision(i)));
        }
        return objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new ModuleReferences(moduleReferencesList));
    }

    private String makeModuleResources(final int length) throws JsonProcessingException {
        final List<ModuleResource> moduleResourceList = new ArrayList<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
            final String moduleName = "module" + i;
            final String revision = makeModuleRevision(i);
            final String yangSource = makeYangSource(moduleName, revision);
            moduleResourceList.add(new ModuleResource(moduleName, revision, yangSource));
        }
        return objectMapper.writeValueAsString(moduleResourceList);
    }

    private String makeModuleRevision(final int index) {
        return LocalDate.of(2021, 1, 1).plusDays(index).toString() + "-" + DEFAULT_TAG;
    }

    private String makeYangSource(final String moduleName, final String moduleRevision) {
        final int paddingSize = TARGET_SIZE * KILOBYTE - MODULE_TEMPLATE.length();
        final String padding = " ".repeat(Math.max(0, paddingSize));
        return MODULE_TEMPLATE.replace("<MODULE_NAME>", moduleName)
            .replace("<MODULE_REVISION>", moduleRevision)
            .replace("<DESCRIPTION>", padding);
    }
}

These changes make the code more readable and self-explanatory, which is especially useful for anyone reading or maintaining the code in the future.:


/**
     * Generates a list of tags with characters ranging from the specified startCharacter to endCharacter.
     *
     * @param startCharacter the starting character for the tags
     * @param endCharacter the ending character for the tags
     * @return a list of tags in the format "tagX" where X is each character from startCharacter to endCharacter
     */


    private static List<String> generateTags(final char startCharacter, final char endCharacter) {
        final List<String> generatedTags = new ArrayList<>();
        for (char currentCharacter = startCharacter; currentCharacter <= endCharacter; currentCharacter++) {
            generatedTags.add("tag" + currentCharacter);
        }
        return generatedTags;
    }

"*".repeat(Math.max(0, paddingSize)):
This method uses Math.max(0, paddingSize) to ensure that the repeat count is never negative.
If paddingSize is negative, it will instead use 0, resulting in an empty string.
Therefore, it safely handles cases where paddingSize could potentially be negative, avoiding exceptions.:


